RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 2 250 Y Dirt CR: 52. Maiden Purse 6000. For Arizona Bred Maidens, Three Years Old and Upward Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JESSTUFFEYED BILLY Broke inwards, veered out sharply at midstretch and impeded LA Z, leveled out nicely. WAGON LION Vied between, drifted in gradually approaching wire and took space away from RJL CASHIN IN, finished strongly. RJL CASHING IN Shuffled out at the break, recovered and closed well, squeezed out of room late from outside rival. FANCY N WILD VIed inside, outfinished. LA Z Impeded midway by inner rival drifting out, lost position. CRUSH THE COMPETITOR Broke outwards and brushed outside rival sharply, ran evenly. FIVE FIVE SIX Shied from outer rival drifting in midway through the lane, never threatened. A STEWARDS INQUIRY WAS HELD INTO THE ACTIONS OF #5 JESSTUFFEYED BILLY AGAINST #7 LA Z. ADDITIONALLY, A TRAINERS' OBJECTION WAS LODGED BY #7 LA Z AGAINST #5 JESSTUFFEYED BILLY. AFTER REVIEW, THE STEWARDS DETERMINED THAT #5 JESSTUFFEYED BILLY CAUSED SIGNIFICANT INTERFERENCE TO #7 LA Z AND #5 JESSTUFFEYED BILLY WAS DISQUALIFIED FROM FIRST TO FIFTH. A SEPARATE STEWARDS INQUIRY WAS HELD INTO #6 WAGON LION. AFTER REVIEW, IT WAS DETERMINED #6 WAGON LION CAUSED SIGNIFICANT INTERFERENCE TO #4 RJL CASHIN IN SHORTLY BEFORE THE WIRE. #6 WAGON LION WAS DISQUALIFIED FROM IT'S NEW PLACING OF FIRST BACK TO SECOND.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 42. Maiden Special Weight Purse 8500. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND OLDER. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LITTLEQUEENOFMEAN Broke on top and led on the rail into the first turn, handled pressure from the outside with ease, shook off challengers at the quarter pole, drew clear on the turn, came home well in control. OJO FELIZ Travelled three wide into the first turn in the second flight, maintained position until moving up five wide at the five-sixteenths pole, moved in the four path on the turn, vied three deep outside of rivals down the stretch, edged rivals for place honors. CANDIED JOULE Moved three wide into the first turn pressing the lead, backed out of line of four at the seven-sixteenths, swung out to the four path into the turn, moved to the three path on the turn, fought between horses through the stretch, evenly approaching and through the wire. MOBILEAGILEHOSTILE Was forced four wide into the first turn, moved three wide up backstretch, cleared to the rail in the run to the stretch, battled inside of rivals, had nothing left at the end. LUCKY CHAMP Broke a touch sluggishly and was a detached trailer, commenced fully six wide at the quarter pole in a move that flattened out through the stretch. WITCHES DANCE Took back into the first turn along the rail in the second flight, stayed within touch up the backstretch, asked at the quarter pole while on the rail but never improved. IGO Let an outer rival clear to the lead and switched to the two path for first turn, pressed the leader up until the quarter pole where he presumably plummeted through the field and was not asked hard in the run home.

ENTRY.NAME: Igo
ENTRY.COMMENT: Switch 2p 1st, press lead, plummeted 1/4, not asked home

ENTRY.NAME: Littlequeenofmean
ENTRY.COMMENT: Led, shook off challenge 1/4, drew clear, in control

ENTRY.NAME: Candied Joule
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3w 1st, backed out 7/16, swung 4w, 3p turn, btwn str, evenly

ENTRY.NAME: Mobileagilehostile
ENTRY.COMMENT: 4w 1st, 3w up backstretch, rail stretch, nothing left

ENTRY.NAME: Lucky Champ
ENTRY.COMMENT: Detached last, commenced 1/4 6w, flattened lane

ENTRY.NAME: Witches Dance
ENTRY.COMMENT: Rail 1st 2nd flight, asked 1/4 on rail, never improved

ENTRY.NAME: Ojo Feliz
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3p 1st, move up 5/16ths 5w, 4p turn, vied 3w str, up for place

RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 5 4F Dirt CR: 73. Allowance Purse 9000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND OLDER WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BRON AND THE BROW Hustled from his inside draw to duel inside for the lead, kept to ask up to the eighth pole when a line of three challengers came to join, fended off the threats and opened up around the sixteenth, held off final pushes from placegetters. MANY AMBITIONS Stalked the pace four wide in the run to the turn, sustained the widest rally in a line of four into the lane, grinded away towards the leader down the stretch, could not muster enough. A BIT MUCH Pushed up after a slightly delayed break to duel outside of rival, tried to keep pace but was shook off by the eventual winner at the eighth pole, re-engaged at the sixteenth and finished with interest between horses. KIND BUT SHE LIES Pressed the dueling leaders three wide up to the turn, fully threatened in the same path at the three-sixteenths pole, backed out into the lane at the eighth pole and flattened out down the stretch. W. WHITEHOUSE Was well outrun early and traveled far off the pace, moved into the turn in the five path, hard asked at the quarter pole, finished up well but way too belatedly, only passed tiring. TOSSAPENNYDOWN Moved up the backstretch off the pace in the five path, called upon at the quarter pole but dropped back and dropped out when the running got going. MEXICAN DREAM Let inner rivals go on, tucked in behind the top flight on the inside paths, fully asked at the three-sixteenths but showed no response.

ENTRY.NAME: Bron and the Brow
ENTRY.COMMENT: Hustled, dueled ins, fend off challengers 1/8, held on

ENTRY.NAME: A Bit Much
ENTRY.COMMENT: Dueled outside, shook off by leader 1/8, willingly lane

ENTRY.NAME: Kind But She Lies
ENTRY.COMMENT: Press 3w, threatened 3w 3/16ths, backed out 1/8, flattened

ENTRY.NAME: Mexican Dream
ENTRY.COMMENT: Tucked in behind inner, ask 3/16ths, never responded

ENTRY.NAME: Many Ambitions
ENTRY.COMMENT: 4w, sustained widest rally, grinded away lane, not enough

ENTRY.NAME: W. Whitehouse
ENTRY.COMMENT: Outrun early, 5p turn, called upon 1/4, belatedly beyond tiring

ENTRY.NAME: Tossapennydown
ENTRY.COMMENT: 5p off pace turn, dropped back when asked 1/4, dropped out

RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 6 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 84. Allowance Purse 9600. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND OLDER WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE JUNE 19, 2022. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DRAW THE FOUL Pressed forward to dispute the lead into the first turn, opened up in a duel up the backside, drew clear at the three-sixteenths in a dominant performance. TAKE CHARGE DEPUTY Stalked in the pocket into the first turn, maintain position up backstretch, swung to the five path for the stretch run, flew home late on the wrong lead. ROYAL JESTER Between in the first turn, backed out of top lane into the backside, moved three wide into the turn, tried determinedly down the lane but gave way late and was caught for place. FIRST COUNT Moved three wide into the first, progressed to duel outside for the lead, traveled in the two path at the quarter pole, had nothing left. EL CHUMELITO Missed the break, moved forward to sit between rivals in the second flight, switched to the six path on the turn, gained mildly through the late stretch. FULL DRAW Was a touch slow to break and trailed early, maintained position but presented a bold rail rally at the quarter pole, never really threatened beyond then. CAPTAIN RED Traveled in the five path on the first turn, moved well out towards the outer rail into the stretch and never menaced. BLUE CHIP BETTY Was forwardly placed in the four path on the first turn, moved two wide up the backside in the second flight, backed out at the three-eighths and was eased from the quarter pole to the wire.

ENTRY.NAME: Take Charge Deputy
ENTRY.COMMENT: Stalk in pocket, swung 5p stretch, wrong lead, flew late

ENTRY.NAME: Full Draw
ENTRY.COMMENT: Touch slow break, last early, rail rally 1/4, no threat

ENTRY.NAME: Draw the Foul
ENTRY.COMMENT: Rail 1st, led inside duel, drew clear 3/16, dominant

ENTRY.NAME: Royal Jester
ENTRY.COMMENT: Btwn 1st, backed out, 3w second, tried lane, caught for place

ENTRY.NAME: El Chumelito
ENTRY.COMMENT: Missed break, between 2nd flight, 6p turn, mildly stretch

ENTRY.NAME: First Count
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3w first, dueled outs lead, 2p 1/4, nothing left

ENTRY.NAME: Blue Chip Betty
ENTRY.COMMENT: 4p turn, 2w backside, backed out 3/8, eased 1/4 to wire

ENTRY.NAME: Captain Red
ENTRY.COMMENT: 5p turn, way out into stretch, no menace

RACE.RACE_TEXT: John K. Goodman S. RILLITO RACE 7 6F Dirt CR: 93. Stakes Purse 20000. FOR HORSES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. No trials and no nomination. An entry fee of $250 to be paid at the time of entry. Horses that have started at the 2023 Rillito meet are preferred. Second preference is earnings in 2022 and 2023. Maidens are least pr eferred. Same owner entries must prefer a horse at the time of entry. Weights: 3 years old . 124, Older . 126.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SPEEDING STYLE Tracked inside in the second rung of runners, maintained position while ridden with confidence, swung to the six path at the three-sixteenths pole to come and threaten, found full gear one-hundred fifty yards from home, kept finding to get up in the final jumps. DEFENSE WINS Dueled two wide into the first turn, made full lead at the eighth pole and kept on through the stretch before being caught in the final strides. WE ALL AGREE Sent hard from the rail draw, dueled inside of rival throughout, dug in when collared at the eighth pole but could not find enough to place better. SANTALUZ DREAMIN Moved three wide into the first turn while stalking the lead, stayed in the same path into the second turn, switched a path further out for clean air into the lane, ran evenly on the wrong lead through the stretch. FANTASTIC DAY Settled well off the pace two wide, did not improve until being asked at the three-eighths pole while having the widest bid, showed far too belated headway. MINISTERSDON'TLIE Forced four wide into the first turn and had to track off the lead, advanced up the backstretch when splitting rivals in the two path at the five-sixteenths pole, switched down to the rail at the quarter pole for a continued rally which was mitigated by better-finishing competitors. BLUE AZUL Had no run early and traveled far off the pace along the rail, asked for more by rider at the three-eighths but failed to improve. BOTERO Settled well off the pace in the rear and never became involved.

ENTRY.COMMENT: Sent rail, duel ins, dug in lane, not quite enough

ENTRY.NAME: Defense Wins
ENTRY.COMMENT: Dueled 2w, led 1/8 through stretch, caught late

ENTRY.COMMENT: 3w first, 3w second, swung 4p lane, evenly stretch

RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 8 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 74. Claiming Purse 7300. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND OLDER THAT HAVE STARTED AT THE 2023 RILLITO PARK MEET AND HAVE NOT FINISHED BETTER THAN THIRD. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $2,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RINGS OF SATURN Broke to the lead and led inside, left the rail open up the backstretch which allowed OMACHE KID through, thwarted off that challenge at the three-sixteenth pole and drew off to a decisive score. OMACHE KID Traveled along the rail in the second flight on the first turn, made a middle move up the rail at the three-eighths pole to threaten for the lead, was fought off into the turn and was a clear second best in the run home. BULLY RIDE Bobbled at the break, moved up the backstretch off the pace along the rail, advanced up the rail at the quarter pole and bested the rest. BIGGER THAN YOU Dueled outside of rival, dropped back at the five-sixteenths, evenly in the run home. EPIC ADVENTURE Moved between in the second flight throughout, never improved. SASSY EDIE Ran into the first turn three wide well in touch of the lead, contended to the quarter pole, gave way. BAJA BRIDGE Settled on the inner off the pace, failed to gain traction. CURRENTLY KRAZY Ran off the pace in the four path, widest both turns, never gained.

ENTRY.COMMENT: Bobble break, inside off pace, adv rail 1/4, bested rest
